The paper deals with the problem of selectivity estimation of boolean queries on binary data sets, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The use of frequent itemsets and linear programming also suggests a connection to data mining and machine learning (cs.DS, cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new concept of safe sets and characterizes them using graph theory, which is a common tool in computer science research (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions a connection between safe sets and Markov Random Fields, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
